# VibeDrift scan exclusions (gitignore syntax).
# Paths here are skipped by `vibedrift scan` and the MCP server, so they
# don't count toward the Vibe Drift Score. Created/edited by
# `vibedrift init` and `vibedrift ignore`. Docs: https://vibedrift.ai/guide
#
# These are test INPUTS and research tooling, not the product. The npm
# package ships only dist/ + bin/ + skills/, so none of this is installed by
# users. eval/ holds the discrimination harness itself plus its
# deliberately-messy negative-class fixture repos (the bulk of eval/);
# test/fixtures and test/calibration are synthetic drift inputs that exist to
# prove the scanner discriminates. The real test suite (test/**/*.test.ts)
# stays in scope.
eval/
test/fixtures/
test/calibration/
